\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sl264\slmult1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f28\fs18\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {
The Narcissistic Personality Disorder (NPD) has been recognised as a separate mental health disorder in the third edition of the Diagnostic and Sta
tistics Manual (DSM) in 1980. Its diagnostic criteria and their interpretation have undergone a major revision in the DSM-III-R [1987] and were substantially revamped in the DSM-IV in 1994. The European ICD-10 basically contains identical language.
\par }\pard \qj \fi170\li0\ri0\sl264\slmult1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {An all-
pervasive pattern of grandiosity (in fantasy or behaviour), need for admiration or adulation and lack of empathy, usually beginning by early adulthood and present in various contexts. Five (or more) of the following criteria must be met:
\par }\pard \qj \fi-142\li312\ri0\sl264\slmult1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin312\itap0 {\cgrid0 \bullet }{\tab Feels grandiose 
and self-importance (e.g., exaggerates achievements and talents to the point of lying, demands to be recognised as superior without commensurate achievements);
\par }{\cgrid0 \bullet }{\tab Is obsessed with fantasies of unlimited success, fame, fearsome power or omnipotence, unequall
ed brilliance (the cerebral narcissist), bodily beauty or sexual performance (the somatic narcissist), or ideal, everlasting, all-conquering love or passion;
\par }{\cgrid0 \bullet }{\tab Firmly convinced that he or she is unique and, being special, can only be understood by, should only be treated by, or associate with, other special or unique, or high-status people (or institutions);
\par }{\cgrid0 \bullet }{\tab Requires excessive admiration, adulation, attention and affirmation \endash  or, failing that, wishes to be feared and to be notorious (Narcissistic Supply);
\par }{\cgrid0 \bullet }{\tab Feels entitled. Expects unreasonable or special and favourable priority treatment. Demands automatic and full compliance with his or her expectations;
\par }{\cgrid0 \bullet }{\tab Is "interpersonally exploitative", i.e., uses others to achieve his or her own ends;
\par }{\cgrid0 \bullet }{\tab Devoid of empathy. Is unable or unwilling to identify with or acknowledge the feelings and needs of others;
\par }{\cgrid0 \bullet }{\tab Constantly envious of others or believes that they feel the same about him or her;
\par }{\cgrid0 \bullet }{\tab Arrogant, haughty behaviours or attitudes coupled with rage when frustrated, contradicted, or confronted.
\par }\pard \qj \fi170\li0\ri0\sl264\slmult1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {The language in the criteria above is based on or summarised from:
